1. Leaving a Detailed Voicemail 

Be clear about:
- Who you are  
- Why you're calling  
- How the recipient can reach you  
- Your availability  

Keep the message concise but informative.

Professional Phrases

Example 1:
"Hello Anjali, this is Ravi Kumar from InfoTech Solutions. I’m calling to follow up on our meeting last week regarding the project proposal. I’d like to discuss the next steps and clarify a few points. Please call me back at 9999999999. I’ll be available until 5 PM today. Thank you."

Example 2:
"Good afternoon, Priya. This is Aditya from Pinnacle Industries. I wanted to go over the revised budget that I sent you yesterday. Could you please review it and get back to me? You can reach me at 9999999999. I’ll be in the office all day tomorrow. Looking forward to your feedback."

Example 3:
"Hi Rohan, this is Neha from Bright Minds Consulting. I’m calling to discuss the training schedule we’ve been working on. I have some updates and would appreciate your input. Please give me a call at 9999999999 when you have a moment. Thank you."

Casual Phrases

Example 1:
"Hey Anjali, it’s Ravi from InfoTech. Just following up on our meeting last week about the project proposal. I’d love to chat about the next steps. Call me back at 9999999999 when you can. I’m here until 5 PM today. Thanks!"

Example 2:
"Hi Priya, Aditya here from Pinnacle Industries. Just wanted to discuss the revised budget I sent over yesterday. Let me know what you think! You can reach me at 9999999999. I’ll be in the office all day tomorrow. Talk soon!"

Example 3:
"Hi Rohan, Neha from Bright Minds Consulting. I’ve got some updates on the training schedule. Give me a call at 9999999999 when you have a sec. Thanks!"

2. Asking for a Callback

Quick Tip:
Make it easy for the recipient to return your call by stating your name,
phone number, and a brief reason for the callback. Be polite but direct in
your message.

Professional Phrases

Example 1:
"Hello Kavita, this is Arun from FutureTech. I’m calling to discuss the upcoming product launch. Please return my call at 9999999999 at your earliest convenience. Thank you."

Example 2:
"Hi Rahul, this is Sunita from Global Enterprises. I’d like to talk with you about the contract renewal. Could you please give me a call back at 9999999999 when you’re available? I appreciate it."

Example 3:
"Good morning, Shweta. This is Vikram from Innovate Corp. I wanted to connect with you regarding the client presentation. Please return my call at 9999999999. I’ll be available until 4 PM."

Casual Phrases

Example 1:
"Hey Kavita, it’s Arun from FutureTech. Just wanted to chat about the product launch. Call me back at 9999999999 when you get a chance. Thanks!"

Example 2:
"Hi Rahul, Sunita here from Global Enterprises. Let’s talk about the contract renewal. Give me a call at 9999999999 when you’re free. Appreciate it!"

Example 3:
"Hi Shweta, Vikram from Innovate Corp here. I wanted to go over the client presentation. Call me back at 9999999999 when you can. I’m here till 4 PM."

3. Following Up After Leaving a Voicemail

Quick Tip:
When following up, remind the recipient of your previous voicemail and
share your contact details again. Keep the message short and show your
willingness to discuss further.

Professional Phrases

Example 1:
"Hello Raj, this is Aditi from Apex Solutions. I left you a voicemail yesterday regarding the team meeting next week. I’m following up to see if you had a chance to listen to it. Please let me know if you’re available for a call today. You can reach me at 9999999999. Thank you."

Example 2:
"Hi Deepak, this is Shreya from Zenith Corporation. Just wanted to follow up on the voicemail I left regarding the project update. Please call me back at 9999999999 when you have a moment. I’d appreciate it."

Example 3:
"Good afternoon, Nisha. This is Karan from Stellar Technologies. I’m following up on the voicemail I left you about the client feedback. Please give me a call back at 9999999999 when you can. Thank you."

Casual Phrases

Example 1:
"Hey Raj, Aditi from Apex Solutions here. Just following up on the voicemail I left you yesterday about the team meeting. Let me know if you’re free to chat today. Call me at 9999999999. Thanks!"

Example 2:
"Hi Deepak, Shreya from Zenith Corporation. Just checking in on the voicemail I left about the project update. Call me back at 9999999999 when you can. Appreciate it!"

Example 3:
"Hi Nisha, it’s Karan from Stellar Technologies. Following up on my voicemail about the client feedback. Give me a call at 9999999999 when you’re free. Thanks!"

4. Responding to a Voicemail

Quick Tip:
Acknowledge the voicemail you received, mention when you’re available,
and invite the other person to connect at their convenience. This shows
responsiveness and respect for their time.

Professional Phrases

Example 1:
"Hello Amit, this is Meera from Sunrise Ltd. Thank you for your voicemail regarding the marketing strategy. I’d like to discuss your suggestions further. When would be a good time to connect? You can reach me at 9999999999."

Example 2:
"Hi Sneha, this is Rajesh from NextGen Technologies. I received your voicemail about the budget review. I’m available to talk anytime after 3 PM today. Please call me at 9999999999."

Example 3:
"Good morning, Ravi. This is Divya from Spectrum Consulting. I got your message about the client proposal. I’m free to discuss it this afternoon. Let me know a good time to call, or you can reach me at 9999999999."

Casual Phrases

Example 1:
"Hey Amit, it’s Meera from Sunrise Ltd. Got your voicemail about the marketing strategy. Let’s chat about your suggestions. When’s a good time for you? Call me at 9999999999."

Example 2:
"Hi Sneha, Rajesh from NextGen Technologies here. Got your message about the budget review. I’m free after 3 PM today. Give me a call at 9999999999 when you can."

Example 3:
"Hi Ravi, Divya from Spectrum Consulting. Thanks for your voicemail about the client proposal. I’m free this afternoon to discuss it. Call me at 9999999999 or let me know what works for you."
